The paper proposes a stochastic algorithm for learning representation from relative similarity comparisons, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The algorithm is based on stochastic variance reduced gradient method and introduces a new adaptive step size. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also discusses the theoretical convergence rate and optimization assumptions, which are related to optimization and information theory, respectively. Therefore, cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
